        "### What's the difference?\n",
        "\n",
        "The  `print(x)` function writes the result of `str(x)` to the standard output. In a jupyter notebook, everything written to `stdout` is printed directy below the code cell.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZKTAIvqXq3W1",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "293ca0b5-d964-4df9-b295-0c17c4090334",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 52
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "# Here we write a value to stdout, which is the same thing as print().\n",
        "\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "\n",
        "sys.stdout.write( \"Hello, standard out!\\n\" )\n",
        "print( \"Hello, print!\" )"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Hello, standard out!\n",
            "Hello, print!\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
